description:
Hi there...

Please seed this further on, for a long time, because it's your right as a Christian to do so, and a privilege. Plus it takes the pressure off my seed-machine. And It can use some relief now.. :-)

And for the blind it's the only way besides Braille to actually hear/read the Word of God.

And like Jesus said when they asked Him whether it was right to pay tax to the emperor or not and they showed Him a coin:
- &quot;Whose picture and name is on it?&quot;
- &quot;The Emperor's&quot;
- &quot;Then give the Emperor what is his and God what is God's&quot;

Well, whose Name and face is on the cover of &quot;Jesus of Nazareth&quot;, &quot;Gospel of John&quot;, &quot;Word of Promise - NKJV Dramatized&quot;?
Jesus' face! So give His Words to the world and let the world have their own, if they won't receive these, but at least you are giving people a choice if you help spread His Words in this way.. Right?

Like the description say; this is the New King James Version New Testament Dramatized. I've heard this before, but the sample wasn't very good, so in this upload it's double the bit-rate. That way the voices doesn't sound like they come from a tin-can. Actually resembles more the human voice than a Edison wax-cylinder. It's more like &quot;Your Master's Voice&quot;, actually.. :-)

I must, in all honesty, tell you that I found this (finally) on the net somewhere, and I thank the original uploader &quot;TV_Dude&quot; for it. It was included in the whole Bible as Audio book, then I reassembled it, tagged it properly, and even threw in a little cover art in the tagging. That way it shows what you're listening to on you iPods or what ever you use for heart-washing and cleansing yourselves in the bath of the Water of Life, God's Word. The whole thing fits nicely onto a standard CD too.. In mp3 quality, that is..

The voice of Jesus is that of the actor that portrayed Him in &quot;The Passion of the Christ&quot;, by the way.. Take good care of it. One day the Words in these books and your knowledge of them will be the only thing that stand between you and a heartless world. Treasure this. Make copies. Store some. Give them away. Freely.. :-)

God bless you all.

Verifire.

